Reasoning: The paper deals with information measures and their application in machine learning. The use of entropy and probability distributions suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The experiments on image barycenters and text summarization suggest that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The use of probability distributions and geometric structure suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The experiments on image barycenters suggest that it could belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. Finally, the experiments on mode coverage and generative models suggest that it could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
